1
00:00:14,480 --> 00:00:17,440
♪In the airport lounge
at the break of day♪

2
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:22,200
♪A page of dust beneath my fingers♪

3
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:25,160
♪Filled with stories♪

4
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:28,280
♪That others never got to tell♪

5
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,960
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

6
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:35,600
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

7
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:37,160
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

8
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:40,040
♪The world is split an inch wider♪

9
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:42,600
♪Raise your eyes, face the light♪

10
00:00:42,760 --> 00:00:45,080
♪See the truth, and see the fright♪

11
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:46,800
♪Guard the crack within this door♪

12
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:52,600
♪Keep the way back home
always burning bright♪

13
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:57,040
♪The camera pans
across the boarding crowd♪

14
00:00:57,080 --> 00:00:59,200
♪Some wear a smile,
some have their eyes adrift♪

15
00:00:59,280 --> 00:01:01,440
♪A red suitcase♪

16
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:05,360
♪Tied with faded pasts
and broken prayers♪

17
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:09,360
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

18
00:01:09,480 --> 00:01:12,080
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

19
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:13,960
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

20
00:01:14,040 --> 00:01:17,400
♪It's the heartbeat
echoing the call of law♪

21
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:30,000
[Gimlet Eyes]

22
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:32,960
[Episode 1]

23
00:02:11,440 --> 00:02:12,240
Mentor!

24
00:02:16,520 --> 00:02:17,160
Mentor!

25
00:02:17,640 --> 00:02:18,280
Mentor!

26
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:22,640
Mentor!

27
00:02:28,720 --> 00:02:30,680
You can't catch me.

28
00:02:31,840 --> 00:02:33,600
You can't catch me.

29
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:37,800
You can't catch me.

30
00:02:40,720 --> 00:02:42,520
You can't catch me.

31
00:02:46,720 --> 00:02:48,800
You can't catch me.

32
00:02:54,880 --> 00:02:57,520
[Binhai]

33
00:02:57,520 --> 00:03:01,480
[Four Years Later
2023]

34
00:03:55,320 --> 00:03:56,440
Mr. Shen.

35
00:03:58,440 --> 00:04:00,520
I'm at outbound diversion.

36
00:04:01,600 --> 00:04:02,080
Yes, sir.

37
00:04:02,440 --> 00:04:03,080
On my way.

38
00:04:17,040 --> 00:04:18,040
Stop!

39
00:04:18,280 --> 00:04:20,200
Stop! Thief!

40
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:25,920
Stop! My bag!

41
00:04:30,880 --> 00:04:31,960
Thank you so much.

42
00:04:32,840 --> 00:04:33,840
My bank cards,

43
00:04:33,840 --> 00:04:36,520
ID, and exchanged foreign cash
are all in there.

44
00:04:36,640 --> 00:04:38,920
If I found out overseas my bag was gone,

45
00:04:38,920 --> 00:04:40,280
I'd be in serious trouble.

46
00:04:40,400 --> 00:04:41,240
Glad you're okay.

47
00:04:41,320 --> 00:04:42,680
Thank you, police lady!

48
00:04:43,880 --> 00:04:45,080
I'm not a police officer.

49
00:04:45,360 --> 00:04:46,520
I'm with China Customs.

50
00:04:47,360 --> 00:04:49,160
You all look great in uniform.

51
00:04:49,160 --> 00:04:50,600
Thank you so much!

52
00:04:55,240 --> 00:04:57,000
You know how hard it is
to staff Passenger Inspection?

53
00:04:57,400 --> 00:04:59,080
I know.

54
00:04:59,840 --> 00:05:00,680
Zhang Yu

55
00:05:00,760 --> 00:05:02,960
has a master's in applied psychology.

56
00:05:02,960 --> 00:05:04,440
She speaks four foreign languages.

57
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:05,800
During new recruit training,

58
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:07,040
her memory and observation

59
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:08,760
were top of the class!

60
00:05:10,040 --> 00:05:10,760
Excuse me,

61
00:05:10,960 --> 00:05:12,320
I'm a new officer with airport customs.

62
00:05:12,320 --> 00:05:13,560
Could you tell me how to
get to Passenger Inspection?

63
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:14,600
Turn right here,

64
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:15,360
then right again downstairs.

65
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:15,880
Thank you.

66
00:05:15,880 --> 00:05:16,520
No problem.

67
00:05:23,840 --> 00:05:25,600
She just got out of grad school.

68
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:27,800
Too sheltered, I'm not sure

69
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:29,720
she can handle Passenger Inspection.

70
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:30,760
Besides,

71
00:05:30,760 --> 00:05:32,120
a talent like her

72
00:05:32,120 --> 00:05:33,520
stuck in Passenger Inspection Section I?

73
00:05:33,520 --> 00:05:34,920
That's a waste.

74
00:05:35,520 --> 00:05:36,520
I hear

75
00:05:36,520 --> 00:05:38,480
the Foreign Affairs team
is short-handed.

76
00:05:38,480 --> 00:05:39,480
She speaks four foreign languages.

77
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:41,320
- So... - Stop beating around the bush.

78
00:05:41,320 --> 00:05:41,960
Fine.

79
00:05:43,240 --> 00:05:45,600
I picked her for your section myself.

80
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:47,560
You have to train her well.

81
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:48,280
Me?

82
00:05:48,280 --> 00:05:49,680
You want me to do it?

83
00:05:51,160 --> 00:05:52,640
Eight years in Passenger Inspection,

84
00:05:52,880 --> 00:05:54,320
three years as section chief,

85
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:56,040
and you've never taken a trainee?

86
00:05:56,040 --> 00:05:57,240
Doesn't sound right, huh?

87
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:58,480
The thing is,

88
00:05:58,480 --> 00:06:00,680
I'm not good at training people.

89
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:04,240
Guo Cong, you're more
capable than you think.

90
00:06:04,280 --> 00:06:06,680
You learned that 'spotting people
at a glance' from your mentor,

91
00:06:06,680 --> 00:06:08,880
and you've already surpassed him.

92
00:06:09,920 --> 00:06:10,720
You know

93
00:06:11,160 --> 00:06:12,160
I've got a lot of issues.

94
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:12,760
How about this?

95
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:13,720
I'll take her.

96
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:15,000
Let Dayu and the others do the training.

97
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:17,680
You think I'm asking?

98
00:06:17,680 --> 00:06:18,640
That's an order.

99
00:06:19,760 --> 00:06:21,560
You will train Zhang Yu yourself.

100
00:06:28,960 --> 00:06:30,400
She's not a good fit?

101
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:31,480
You know what?

102
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:33,400
I used to think
you weren't a good fit either.

103
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:34,400
Remember when you joined

104
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:35,920
in your early twenties?

105
00:06:35,960 --> 00:06:36,920
You were reckless.

106
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:38,000
Sloppy.

107
00:06:38,200 --> 00:06:40,480
Want me to go into detail?

108
00:06:40,520 --> 00:06:43,920
Did your Mentor ever give up on you?

109
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:45,040
Sir, no, sir.

110
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:46,120
Pass it on!

111
00:06:46,120 --> 00:06:47,800
If you don't, nothing carries forward!

112
00:06:49,080 --> 00:06:51,200
Your mentor never turned anyone away.

113
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:53,160
And he made something out of you.

114
00:06:58,240 --> 00:06:59,360
You know, your mentor,

115
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:00,760
for Group E, he already…

116
00:07:00,760 --> 00:07:01,360
Sir.

117
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:03,040
I'll take Zhang Yu

118
00:07:03,040 --> 00:07:03,760
as my trainee.

119
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:08,920
Come on in.

120
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:11,200
Sir.

121
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:13,440
Zhang Yu, Section I, reporting for duty.

122
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:15,320
Zhang Yu.

123
00:07:15,320 --> 00:07:16,520
Perfect timing. Come in.

124
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:17,880
Let me introduce you.

125
00:07:18,240 --> 00:07:20,160
This is your section chief,

126
00:07:20,240 --> 00:07:21,240
Guo Cong.

127
00:07:21,840 --> 00:07:23,080
He'll be your mentor.

128
00:07:23,640 --> 00:07:25,360
Best eye in the division.

129
00:07:25,360 --> 00:07:26,720
Learn from him.

130
00:07:27,480 --> 00:07:28,120
Yes, sir.

131
00:07:28,440 --> 00:07:30,120
I won't let you down.

132
00:07:30,320 --> 00:07:32,680
I'll learn from Chief Guo

133
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:34,440
and become a qualified officer.

134
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:35,240
Good.

135
00:07:38,200 --> 00:07:38,880
What are you waiting for?

136
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:40,600
Isn't it time to rotate?

137
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:41,480
Go.

138
00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:42,600
Yes, sir.

139
00:07:45,760 --> 00:07:46,560
Hold on.

140
00:07:47,440 --> 00:07:48,720
In Customs,

141
00:07:48,920 --> 00:07:50,360
you need discipline, focus,

142
00:07:50,520 --> 00:07:51,880
and to stay sharp.

143
00:07:51,880 --> 00:07:52,680
Guo Cong.

144
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:54,000
Got it.

145
00:08:23,840 --> 00:08:25,960
You heard what I said to Mr. Shen?

146
00:08:26,360 --> 00:08:27,120
I did.

147
00:08:27,120 --> 00:08:28,200
You don't want me here.

148
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:29,800
Well, you're pretty blunt.

149
00:08:30,120 --> 00:08:31,120
It's not that.

150
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:32,400
I'm just not sure you'll last.

151
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:33,240
Why?

152
00:08:33,360 --> 00:08:34,360
In Passenger Inspection,

153
00:08:34,360 --> 00:08:35,800
there are no regular hours.

154
00:08:35,920 --> 00:08:37,040
We're on call 24/7.

155
00:08:37,160 --> 00:08:38,760
You stay indoors all day,

156
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:40,440
no sun, year-round.

157
00:08:40,680 --> 00:08:42,280
Overtime, night shifts, humidity.

158
00:08:42,400 --> 00:08:44,280
Not exactly great for your skin.

159
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:46,560
You'll take blame for things

160
00:08:46,680 --> 00:08:47,880
you didn't do.

161
00:08:48,240 --> 00:08:49,360
If one day you can't take it,

162
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:50,720
and want to quit or transfer,

163
00:08:50,720 --> 00:08:52,680
I'll fully support whatever you decide.

164
00:08:55,760 --> 00:08:57,480
I appreciate that, sir.

165
00:08:57,480 --> 00:08:58,640
But I won't need it.

166
00:08:58,720 --> 00:08:59,800
If others can do it,

167
00:08:59,800 --> 00:09:00,680
so can I.

168
00:09:00,920 --> 00:09:01,920
And besides,

169
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:05,000
no sun all year?

170
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:06,960
That'll save me a fortune on sunscreen.

171
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:10,360
You judged me

172
00:09:10,360 --> 00:09:11,560
before you knew me.

173
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:13,440
That's presuming guilt.

174
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:16,040
Is that really your standard
of judgment in Passenger Inspection?

175
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:18,880
I hope I'm wrong.

176
00:09:19,920 --> 00:09:20,680
[Huayan Airport Customs, Binhai]

177
00:09:20,680 --> 00:09:22,920
[Huayan Airport Customs, Binhai]
Everyone, we've got a new member.

178
00:09:22,920 --> 00:09:24,520
[Huayan Airport Customs, Binhai]
Allow me to introduce Zhang Yu.

179
00:09:27,960 --> 00:09:28,840
Hi everyone.

180
00:09:28,840 --> 00:09:30,000
I'm Zhang Yu.

181
00:09:30,040 --> 00:09:31,480
I look forward to learning from you.

182
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:33,760
Finally, a new face!

183
00:09:33,760 --> 00:09:35,840
- Welcome! - Welcome!

184
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:39,560
Hey there, Zhang.

185
00:09:39,720 --> 00:09:40,720
I'm Deng Hongxia.

186
00:09:40,880 --> 00:09:41,760
In this section,

187
00:09:41,760 --> 00:09:44,120
I'm the oldest
and have been here the longest.

188
00:09:44,160 --> 00:09:45,280
Just call me Deng.

189
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:46,320
Everyone does.

190
00:09:46,400 --> 00:09:47,280
Hi, Deng.

191
00:09:48,560 --> 00:09:49,680
Relax.

192
00:09:49,840 --> 00:09:50,360
Have a seat.

193
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:52,720
Alright, everyone, pre-shift briefing.

194
00:09:53,280 --> 00:09:53,960
Mr. Guo,

195
00:09:53,960 --> 00:09:54,560
Zhang Yu

196
00:09:54,560 --> 00:09:55,520
is officially

197
00:09:55,520 --> 00:09:56,920
joining Section I today.

198
00:09:56,920 --> 00:09:59,320
Shouldn't we do introductions?

199
00:09:59,320 --> 00:10:00,760
That's not on the briefing agenda.

200
00:10:00,760 --> 00:10:01,560
Dayu,

201
00:10:01,680 --> 00:10:03,040
go over today's flights

202
00:10:03,040 --> 00:10:03,920
and passenger flow.

203
00:10:03,920 --> 00:10:04,320
Sure thing.

204
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:05,000
It's fine, sit.

205
00:10:13,040 --> 00:10:13,800
Zhang Yu,

206
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:15,320
I'm Zhang Dayu.

207
00:10:15,320 --> 00:10:17,680
Today is the first day
of the Mid-Autumn break.

208
00:10:17,880 --> 00:10:20,160
We have 89 international flights
in and out today.

209
00:10:20,240 --> 00:10:21,800
According to data,

210
00:10:21,880 --> 00:10:22,680
passenger volume

211
00:10:22,680 --> 00:10:24,160
is about 24,500.

212
00:10:24,160 --> 00:10:26,640
Peak hours are
from 10:00 PM to 11:00 PM,

213
00:10:26,640 --> 00:10:28,800
and the following morning from 6:30 AM

214
00:10:28,800 --> 00:10:29,760
to 8:30 AM.

215
00:10:30,280 --> 00:10:31,200
We got a tip.

216
00:10:31,200 --> 00:10:31,800
Tomorrow morning,

217
00:10:31,800 --> 00:10:34,200
mules will smuggle a batch of gold out.

218
00:10:34,440 --> 00:10:36,880
They'll be on flight ADF331.

219
00:10:36,880 --> 00:10:37,680
Departs at

220
00:10:37,680 --> 00:10:39,200
8:35 AM tomorrow.

221
00:10:40,680 --> 00:10:42,960
That means clearance

222
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:45,480
lines up with
the shift handover to Section III.

223
00:10:46,880 --> 00:10:48,720
They picked this flight

224
00:10:48,840 --> 00:10:50,040
for a reason.

225
00:10:50,120 --> 00:10:51,280
And it's gold again.

226
00:10:51,280 --> 00:10:51,720
This month,

227
00:10:51,720 --> 00:10:53,960
we've had several gold cases.

228
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:55,320
But right now,

229
00:10:55,360 --> 00:10:57,680
the price spread is inverted.

230
00:10:57,720 --> 00:11:00,520
Moving gold out would lose money.

231
00:11:01,080 --> 00:11:02,320
Whatever their motive,

232
00:11:02,360 --> 00:11:03,560
our job is clear:

233
00:11:03,760 --> 00:11:05,840
nothing gets through on our watch.

234
00:11:07,120 --> 00:11:09,640
Now, let me go over
today's post assignments.

235
00:11:09,880 --> 00:11:11,680
Qiang and Wei, Health Quarantine.

236
00:11:11,720 --> 00:11:13,760
Zhen and Lyu Xiaoyan,
Declaration Counter.

237
00:11:14,040 --> 00:11:15,600
Non-declare Lane, three teams.

238
00:11:15,760 --> 00:11:18,040
Team one, Jiang Shihuo
and Yan Bowen, diversion post.

239
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:19,520
Dayu, lead team two,

240
00:11:19,520 --> 00:11:20,600
X-ray screening.

241
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:22,520
Deng and Long, Inspection Counter.

242
00:11:22,520 --> 00:11:23,240
I'll be mobile,

243
00:11:23,240 --> 00:11:24,080
cover all areas.

244
00:11:24,120 --> 00:11:24,800
Clear?

245
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:25,400
Yes, sir.

246
00:11:25,440 --> 00:11:25,920
Sync time.

247
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:27,640
It's 4:45.

248
00:11:27,640 --> 00:11:29,200
Rotate in 15.

249
00:11:30,080 --> 00:11:31,920
W-where should I be?

250
00:11:34,840 --> 00:11:36,120
It's your first day.

251
00:11:36,240 --> 00:11:37,320
Just observe for now.

252
00:11:37,360 --> 00:11:38,200
Watch and learn.

253
00:11:38,880 --> 00:11:39,960
Okay, take positions.

254
00:11:46,120 --> 00:11:46,880
Zhang Yu.

255
00:11:47,720 --> 00:11:48,360
Hi.

256
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:49,480
I'm Lyu Xiaoyan,

257
00:11:49,640 --> 00:11:51,160
Deng's trainee.

258
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:52,520
Welcome to Section I.

259
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:54,040
Hi, Xiaoyan.

260
00:11:54,360 --> 00:11:55,840
You've been here longer.

261
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:57,840
I'll learn from you.

262
00:11:57,960 --> 00:11:59,880
Barely, just a year.

263
00:12:00,360 --> 00:12:01,040
Don't be nervous.

264
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:02,440
First day, you'll get used to it.

265
00:12:04,880 --> 00:12:07,800
Don't mind Mr. Guo.

266
00:12:07,800 --> 00:12:09,280
He's like that at work.

267
00:12:09,280 --> 00:12:11,880
Off duty, he's nice.

268
00:12:14,520 --> 00:12:15,760
Come on, let's go.

269
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:21,280
Here.

270
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:22,920
Looks new.

271
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:24,920
See ya.

272
00:12:27,520 --> 00:12:28,480
Let's go, Zhang Yu.

273
00:12:37,120 --> 00:12:38,920
Go get 'em, Zhang Yu!

274
00:12:39,560 --> 00:12:41,240
Zhang Yu, what are you mumbling?

275
00:13:33,680 --> 00:13:35,280
Section I, attention!

276
00:13:35,280 --> 00:13:36,360
Left face!

277
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:38,440
Dress right!

278
00:13:41,160 --> 00:13:42,600
Eyes front!

279
00:13:46,400 --> 00:13:47,760
All units,

280
00:13:48,080 --> 00:13:49,440
prepare to rotate.

281
00:13:49,600 --> 00:13:50,440
Salute!

282
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:52,200
At ease.

283
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:53,760
Section II, dismissed.

284
00:13:53,760 --> 00:13:55,200
Yes, sir.

285
00:13:57,720 --> 00:13:58,640
Section I,

286
00:13:58,960 --> 00:13:59,520
take positions.

287
00:13:59,520 --> 00:14:00,760
Yes, sir.

288
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:27,840
Dayu,

289
00:14:28,760 --> 00:14:29,320
look.

290
00:14:38,640 --> 00:14:39,640
Typical newbie.

291
00:14:39,960 --> 00:14:40,760
Yeah.

292
00:15:01,040 --> 00:15:01,880
Hey, Dayu.

293
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:05,040
Where am I supposed to be?

294
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:06,080
Come over here.

295
00:15:06,480 --> 00:15:07,600
- Sit here. - Okay.

296
00:15:11,320 --> 00:15:12,320
Zhang Yu.

297
00:15:13,760 --> 00:15:14,760
Tell me,

298
00:15:15,240 --> 00:15:16,800
what did I tell you to do?

299
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:20,080
T-to observe.

300
00:15:20,840 --> 00:15:22,880
I said watch and learn,

301
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:24,880
not wander around
like you own the place.

302
00:15:25,440 --> 00:15:26,200
In that uniform,

303
00:15:26,200 --> 00:15:27,760
you think that's appropriate?

304
00:15:27,840 --> 00:15:28,640
Mr. Guo,

305
00:15:29,200 --> 00:15:30,720
you said watch and learn,

306
00:15:30,800 --> 00:15:33,040
you didn't say where.

307
00:15:34,280 --> 00:15:36,400
Maybe you could mark a spot,

308
00:15:36,520 --> 00:15:37,360
tell me where,

309
00:15:37,360 --> 00:15:39,440
and I-I promise I won't move.

310
00:15:39,560 --> 00:15:41,000
Too much Monkey King.

311
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:42,440
Draw a magic circle, really?

312
00:15:46,240 --> 00:15:48,600
Is it appropriate to be
drifting around in that uniform?

313
00:15:53,440 --> 00:15:54,320
Stand over there.

314
00:15:55,840 --> 00:15:56,600
Yes, sir.

315
00:15:59,480 --> 00:16:00,440
It's fine, sit.

316
00:16:00,440 --> 00:16:01,680
Just stand?

317
00:16:01,840 --> 00:16:03,080
Watch the X-ray.

318
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:10,640
Ignore him.

319
00:16:10,640 --> 00:16:11,520
All bark, no bite.

320
00:16:11,840 --> 00:16:13,360
Sit, it's fine.

321
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:14,520
I'm good.

322
00:16:14,560 --> 00:16:15,480
I'll stand.

323
00:16:41,120 --> 00:16:41,920
What do you think?

324
00:16:42,920 --> 00:16:43,720
Huge!

325
00:16:44,120 --> 00:16:45,120
Li,

326
00:16:45,920 --> 00:16:47,760
nice place!

327
00:16:48,840 --> 00:16:51,040
When do I get a place like that?

328
00:16:52,320 --> 00:16:54,080
Drop a few girlfriends,

329
00:16:55,360 --> 00:16:57,080
you'll get there.

330
00:16:58,400 --> 00:16:59,800
Can you blame me?

331
00:17:00,040 --> 00:17:01,640
I deal in luxury goods.

332
00:17:01,880 --> 00:17:03,520
Pretty girls surround me

333
00:17:03,880 --> 00:17:04,800
like predators.

334
00:17:04,800 --> 00:17:05,840
What can I do?

335
00:17:06,960 --> 00:17:07,800
Xiao Dabao,

336
00:17:08,160 --> 00:17:09,560
'predators',

337
00:17:09,840 --> 00:17:11,440
nice choice of words.

338
00:17:11,440 --> 00:17:14,720
To them, you're just prey.

339
00:17:16,080 --> 00:17:16,840
Xiao Dabao.

340
00:17:17,040 --> 00:17:18,320
I'm telling you straight,

341
00:17:18,800 --> 00:17:20,480
I don't care what you do out there.

342
00:17:21,240 --> 00:17:23,160
But any woman tied to the job

343
00:17:23,320 --> 00:17:24,960
can't run as a mule again.

344
00:17:25,600 --> 00:17:27,800
If they lead back to us,

345
00:17:28,520 --> 00:17:30,440
I won't be the only one after you.

346
00:17:30,640 --> 00:17:32,040
Mr. E will too.

347
00:17:32,720 --> 00:17:33,920
Relax. I got it.

348
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:35,960
I know the line.

349
00:17:37,640 --> 00:17:38,200
Li,

350
00:17:40,520 --> 00:17:41,880
that Mr. E…

351
00:17:43,120 --> 00:17:44,440
We still haven't

352
00:17:45,040 --> 00:17:45,960
seen him.

353
00:17:47,080 --> 00:17:48,320
Who on earth

354
00:17:48,360 --> 00:17:49,440
is he?

355
00:17:53,040 --> 00:17:54,120
No idea.

356
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:56,880
All I know is he's
someone we can't cross.

357
00:17:59,480 --> 00:18:00,720
Back then,

358
00:18:01,680 --> 00:18:03,240
he took Sa Ziyi out.

359
00:18:06,400 --> 00:18:07,880
But honestly, I don't care who he is.

360
00:18:08,160 --> 00:18:09,200
All I care about is

361
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:10,440
that he made us more money

362
00:18:10,640 --> 00:18:12,000
than we dreamed.

363
00:18:12,560 --> 00:18:13,320
That's enough.

364
00:18:14,320 --> 00:18:15,240
So,

365
00:18:15,280 --> 00:18:17,240
as long as we don't cross his line,

366
00:18:17,800 --> 00:18:19,160
we're fine.

367
00:18:22,680 --> 00:18:23,560
All units, heads up,

368
00:18:23,560 --> 00:18:24,480
passengers incoming.

369
00:18:40,760 --> 00:18:41,320
Zhang Yu,

370
00:18:41,640 --> 00:18:42,880
priority flight info sheet.

371
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:18,760
This way, please.

372
00:19:29,240 --> 00:19:30,240
Close your eyes.

373
00:19:30,240 --> 00:19:31,240
Deep breath.

374
00:19:31,720 --> 00:19:32,640
Take five.

375
00:19:32,680 --> 00:19:33,760
You're getting crowd dizzy.

376
00:19:39,440 --> 00:19:40,240
Mr. Guo,

377
00:19:40,720 --> 00:19:42,000
what's 'crowd dizzy'?

378
00:19:42,320 --> 00:19:43,840
You ever play CS growing up?

379
00:19:44,480 --> 00:19:45,080
Yeah.

380
00:19:45,080 --> 00:19:45,920
This way, please.

381
00:19:46,160 --> 00:19:48,480
When it gets crowded in the game,

382
00:19:48,880 --> 00:19:50,280
and your aim's all over the place,

383
00:19:50,280 --> 00:19:51,400
you get dizzy, right?

384
00:19:51,400 --> 00:19:52,240
This way, thanks.

385
00:19:53,920 --> 00:19:54,560
Yeah.

386
00:19:54,800 --> 00:19:56,080
Same thing here.

387
00:19:56,720 --> 00:19:57,920
In this lane,

388
00:19:57,920 --> 00:19:59,920
hundreds pass by you.

389
00:20:00,080 --> 00:20:01,320
Their expressions change.

390
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:02,480
They're constantly moving.

391
00:20:02,920 --> 00:20:04,480
If you stare at every face,

392
00:20:04,480 --> 00:20:05,400
you'll get dizzy fast.

393
00:20:05,520 --> 00:20:06,640
This way, thank you.

394
00:20:06,840 --> 00:20:07,880
So what should I do?

395
00:20:07,960 --> 00:20:09,160
There's a trick.

396
00:20:09,840 --> 00:20:11,440
Broaden your view.

397
00:20:12,040 --> 00:20:13,560
Don't fixate on one spot.

398
00:20:14,200 --> 00:20:16,600
Let your eyes pick targets.

399
00:20:17,160 --> 00:20:18,920
When you switch targets,

400
00:20:18,960 --> 00:20:20,120
go point to point.

401
00:20:20,440 --> 00:20:21,880
Don't let your eyes wander.

402
00:20:23,360 --> 00:20:23,920
Alright.

403
00:20:24,320 --> 00:20:25,840
Open your eyes. Try it.

404
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:28,360
Hello. This way, thanks.

405
00:20:31,440 --> 00:20:33,000
Sir, this way please.

406
00:20:43,320 --> 00:20:44,040
Hello.

407
00:21:15,720 --> 00:21:17,040
Got a new face in the circle.

408
00:21:31,480 --> 00:21:31,960
Mr. Guo,

409
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:33,760
the last outbound flight of the day

410
00:21:33,760 --> 00:21:34,560
has departed.

411
00:21:34,840 --> 00:21:36,120
Get everyone some rest.

412
00:21:36,280 --> 00:21:36,880
Sure.

413
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:38,480
Let's head back to the duty room.

414
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:39,400
Good job.

415
00:21:39,400 --> 00:21:40,000
Zhang Yu,

416
00:21:40,280 --> 00:21:40,840
let's go.

417
00:21:40,840 --> 00:21:42,000
I'll take you to the rest area.

418
00:21:42,080 --> 00:21:42,680
Okay.

419
00:21:47,360 --> 00:21:48,040
Zhang Yu,

420
00:21:48,200 --> 00:21:49,040
one moment.

421
00:21:51,280 --> 00:21:52,840
Someone's getting a lesson from Mr. Guo.

422
00:21:52,840 --> 00:21:53,600
I'm out.

423
00:21:53,920 --> 00:21:55,200
Bye! See you in the rest area.

424
00:22:02,800 --> 00:22:04,800
This lane's 50 meters.

425
00:22:04,920 --> 00:22:06,240
About 100 steps.

426
00:22:06,560 --> 00:22:08,640
This is where we work every day.

427
00:22:09,280 --> 00:22:10,800
You've seen the conditions

428
00:22:10,960 --> 00:22:12,720
and felt the workload.

429
00:22:13,160 --> 00:22:13,960
So,

430
00:22:14,200 --> 00:22:15,320
this job

431
00:22:15,400 --> 00:22:17,120
is not as simple as it looks.

432
00:22:21,320 --> 00:22:23,120
Mr. Guo, don't worry.

433
00:22:23,880 --> 00:22:25,560
I don't quit.

434
00:22:25,800 --> 00:22:27,560
I can handle it.

435
00:22:28,560 --> 00:22:29,840
I personally requested

436
00:22:29,840 --> 00:22:31,880
the transfer here from Mr. Zhao.

437
00:22:31,920 --> 00:22:33,120
If I can't hack it,

438
00:22:33,440 --> 00:22:34,440
you can pull me out.

439
00:22:36,040 --> 00:22:36,960
Deal.

440
00:22:40,240 --> 00:22:41,320
My mentor gave me

441
00:22:41,320 --> 00:22:42,800
my first lesson right here,

442
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:44,720
same as everyone's first lesson.

443
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:46,400
This lane in front of you

444
00:22:46,600 --> 00:22:47,640
is the border gate we guard

445
00:22:47,640 --> 00:22:48,680
around the clock.

446
00:22:49,880 --> 00:22:51,000
Within these hundred steps,

447
00:22:51,080 --> 00:22:52,680
tens of thousands pass through daily.

448
00:22:53,240 --> 00:22:54,400
Among them,

449
00:22:54,560 --> 00:22:56,200
there's always someone

450
00:22:56,280 --> 00:22:57,560
breaking the law.

451
00:22:57,640 --> 00:22:58,760
Our job

452
00:22:58,880 --> 00:23:01,120
is to spot them right here.

453
00:23:01,480 --> 00:23:04,960
So, what do you feel right now?

454
00:23:11,280 --> 00:23:13,280
As long as we stand guard,

455
00:23:13,680 --> 00:23:16,040
no enemy will ever make it past us.

456
00:23:18,040 --> 00:23:18,640
Cong,

457
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:20,600
before Customs,

458
00:23:20,680 --> 00:23:22,560
I spent 12 years guarding the border

459
00:23:22,800 --> 00:23:24,280
and training soldiers.

460
00:23:25,560 --> 00:23:27,360
Every year, new recruits came in,

461
00:23:27,600 --> 00:23:29,120
and I told them one thing:

462
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:31,720
As long as we stand guard,

463
00:23:32,160 --> 00:23:33,720
no enemy will ever make it past us.

464
00:23:34,320 --> 00:23:36,120
Now I'm passing that on to you.

465
00:23:37,240 --> 00:23:37,760
Remember,

466
00:23:38,800 --> 00:23:39,600
this

467
00:23:41,160 --> 00:23:42,520
is the line we defend.

468
00:23:57,800 --> 00:23:58,480
Deng,

469
00:23:59,480 --> 00:24:01,440
duty room in five minutes.

470
00:24:01,600 --> 00:24:02,560
Got it.

471
00:24:03,400 --> 00:24:04,200
Up.

472
00:24:04,960 --> 00:24:05,800
Xiaoyan, hurry up.

473
00:24:18,440 --> 00:24:19,400
Here, take this.

474
00:24:20,440 --> 00:24:21,480
Come on, Xiaoyan.

475
00:24:21,480 --> 00:24:23,080
One sec, tying my shoe!

476
00:24:23,480 --> 00:24:24,720
Always dragging your feet.

477
00:24:30,240 --> 00:24:32,480
One week ago,
a biopharmaceutical company

478
00:24:32,480 --> 00:24:33,160
reported

479
00:24:33,160 --> 00:24:35,120
a stolen blood genetic sample
related to a hereditary disease.

480
00:24:35,200 --> 00:24:36,040
Based on intel,

481
00:24:36,040 --> 00:24:38,400
the suspect will fly out today

482
00:24:38,400 --> 00:24:39,520
with it.

483
00:24:39,760 --> 00:24:41,840
Flight ADF331.

484
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:43,560
Dayu, details.

485
00:24:43,680 --> 00:24:45,160
Inbound flight

486
00:24:45,160 --> 00:24:46,360
[Binhai Huayan Airport Customs]
is ADF330.

487
00:24:46,480 --> 00:24:47,240
[01. Flight ADF330 Info]
At 6:20 AM,

488
00:24:47,240 --> 00:24:48,200
it arrives from Modiya,

489
00:24:48,200 --> 00:24:49,200
a Southeast Asian resort destination.

490
00:24:49,400 --> 00:24:50,320
Two-hour layover,

491
00:24:50,320 --> 00:24:52,320
then departs for Seattle at 8:35 AM.

492
00:24:52,400 --> 00:24:53,440
Aircraft is

493
00:24:53,440 --> 00:24:54,560
an A380,

494
00:24:54,560 --> 00:24:56,040
capacity 555, three cabins.

495
00:24:56,040 --> 00:24:57,960
[8:35 Binhai - Seattle Passengers: 472]
Based on bookings,

496
00:24:57,960 --> 00:24:59,720
[8:35 Binhai - Seattle Passengers: 472]
the expected passenger count is 472.

497
00:25:01,240 --> 00:25:01,920
Zhang Yu,

498
00:25:02,560 --> 00:25:05,040
do you realize how critical
these genetic samples are?

499
00:25:08,920 --> 00:25:10,200
Our country

500
00:25:10,200 --> 00:25:13,640
has vast genetic resources,

501
00:25:13,680 --> 00:25:15,280
including

502
00:25:15,280 --> 00:25:17,560
key disease lineages.

503
00:25:17,720 --> 00:25:18,560
Without approval,

504
00:25:18,560 --> 00:25:20,320
no organization or individual

505
00:25:20,400 --> 00:25:21,120
may

506
00:25:21,120 --> 00:25:22,240
collect,

507
00:25:22,240 --> 00:25:24,440
gather, trade, export, or take them out,

508
00:25:24,440 --> 00:25:25,920
or in any other way

509
00:25:25,920 --> 00:25:27,320
share them externally.

510
00:25:27,880 --> 00:25:29,240
You know your regs.

511
00:25:30,480 --> 00:25:32,440
Knowing the stakes matters.

512
00:25:32,680 --> 00:25:34,080
You're on diversion today,

513
00:25:34,440 --> 00:25:35,560
with one task only:

514
00:25:35,720 --> 00:25:38,120
find the person
carrying this genetic sample.

515
00:25:39,000 --> 00:25:39,880
Me?

516
00:25:39,880 --> 00:25:40,680
Yes.

517
00:25:41,120 --> 00:25:42,280
Just me?

518
00:25:42,280 --> 00:25:43,440
Yes, just you.

519
00:25:43,440 --> 00:25:44,400
Can you handle it?

520
00:25:46,320 --> 00:25:47,440
I'll do my best.

521
00:25:48,120 --> 00:25:49,560
Yes or no.

522
00:25:49,560 --> 00:25:51,240
'Do my best' doesn't cut it.

523
00:25:59,920 --> 00:26:00,560
Yes.

524
00:26:00,680 --> 00:26:01,320
Good.

525
00:26:01,880 --> 00:26:02,560
Bowen,

526
00:26:02,760 --> 00:26:04,960
brief her on the container.

527
00:26:05,520 --> 00:26:05,880
Sure.

528
00:26:06,080 --> 00:26:07,400
I'll step out.

529
00:26:07,640 --> 00:26:08,680
Get some rest while you can.

530
00:26:12,640 --> 00:26:13,480
Mentor,

531
00:26:14,080 --> 00:26:16,320
Mr. Guo gave Zhang Yu
a task this critical.

532
00:26:16,320 --> 00:26:18,280
Isn't he basically
setting her up to fail?

533
00:26:18,400 --> 00:26:20,160
He wouldn't go that far, right?

534
00:26:20,800 --> 00:26:22,160
Stop gossiping.

535
00:26:22,800 --> 00:26:24,040
Mind your own work.

536
00:26:41,880 --> 00:26:44,040
Qian Shengkai, 35.

537
00:26:44,240 --> 00:26:46,920
Family man, one daughter,
electrical engineer.

538
00:26:47,000 --> 00:26:48,600
Lost big on crypto.

539
00:26:48,920 --> 00:26:51,560
Half a million in debt.
Won't admit defeat.

540
00:27:16,560 --> 00:27:17,560
Sorry, did I wake you?

541
00:27:19,280 --> 00:27:20,520
Why so early?

542
00:27:21,040 --> 00:27:22,160
Wanna go back to sleep?

543
00:27:22,560 --> 00:27:23,760
It's an international flight.

544
00:27:24,320 --> 00:27:25,640
Gotta clear customs.

545
00:27:25,880 --> 00:27:26,960
Better safe than rushed.

546
00:27:44,600 --> 00:27:45,160
Zhang Yu,

547
00:27:45,640 --> 00:27:46,640
let me walk you through

548
00:27:46,760 --> 00:27:47,760
the genetic sample container.

549
00:27:48,520 --> 00:27:49,120
Sure.

550
00:27:54,240 --> 00:27:55,600
This compact sample container

551
00:27:55,600 --> 00:27:56,840
is about lipstick-sized,

552
00:27:56,880 --> 00:27:58,520
a sealed unit
with built-in refrigeration.

553
00:27:58,520 --> 00:27:59,960
The internal design is highly precise.

554
00:28:00,800 --> 00:28:03,280
Inside is a micro test tube

555
00:28:03,480 --> 00:28:05,920
secured in a base rack.

556
00:28:06,200 --> 00:28:08,760
The rack houses
an active cooling system.

557
00:28:08,880 --> 00:28:10,480
The lid is linked

558
00:28:10,480 --> 00:28:12,320
by external mechanical latches

559
00:28:12,320 --> 00:28:13,680
to the inner tube.

560
00:28:13,960 --> 00:28:15,200
This type of container

561
00:28:15,200 --> 00:28:17,360
can only be opened inside a designated

562
00:28:17,360 --> 00:28:18,120
genetic analysis chamber.

563
00:28:18,120 --> 00:28:19,240
If it's opened outside,

564
00:28:19,280 --> 00:28:20,440
changes in temperature,

565
00:28:20,600 --> 00:28:22,280
humidity, and oxygen levels

566
00:28:22,280 --> 00:28:24,360
will degrade the sample beyond use.

567
00:28:24,800 --> 00:28:26,080
In other words,

568
00:28:26,280 --> 00:28:29,360
it won't be repackaged.

569
00:28:29,360 --> 00:28:31,840
It has to leave Binhai
in its original container.

570
00:28:31,880 --> 00:28:32,560
Exactly.

571
00:28:32,960 --> 00:28:33,920
So could a smuggler

572
00:28:33,920 --> 00:28:36,040
wrap it in dense materials,

573
00:28:36,040 --> 00:28:39,280
like gold, silver,

574
00:28:39,280 --> 00:28:41,080
lead, or tin,

575
00:28:41,320 --> 00:28:43,600
to block X-rays?

576
00:28:44,120 --> 00:28:45,200
Not a chance.

577
00:28:45,560 --> 00:28:46,320
Look,

578
00:28:46,400 --> 00:28:48,160
dense materials thicker than two

579
00:28:48,160 --> 00:28:48,800
to three millimeters

580
00:28:48,800 --> 00:28:50,880
can block X-rays,

581
00:28:50,880 --> 00:28:51,880
but they'll show up as

582
00:28:51,880 --> 00:28:53,800
a dark blur on the scan.

